White, with the idea to play Nc4 next.} (13. Be3 c5 14. Nc3 $14 {1-0 (35)
Maghsoodloo,P (2701)-Ivanisevic,I (2601) Belgrade 2022}) 13... Ba6 14. Be3 c5
15. Nc4 Bxc4 16. Qxc4 $16 {With the bishop pair and Black's weaknesses on c5
and a7, White has a huge advantage.}) (6... Nc6 7. cxd5 $1 (7. Nxd4 Bc5 {
This is a different theoretical continuation.}) 7... exd5 $6 (7... Nxd5 8. Nxd4
$14 {[%cal Gb1c3,Gg2a8]}) 8. Nxd4 {This is a bad version of the Tarrasch for
