possible.}) (13. Nxe6 {This is a simple option that White can play.} fxe6 14.
Nb5 Qd7 15. Nd4 $16) 13... Na5 14. Qc2 {[%cal Gf1d1]} Rc8 (14... Nc4 15. Bg5 h6
16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. Rfd1 $16 {[%csl Rd5] There is a lot of pressure on the
d5-pawn.}) 15. Rfd1 $16 {All of White's pieces are well-placed and the d5-pawn
